# Homepage First Workflow

- For a new client site, start with homepage design before building secondary pages.
- Treat the homepage as the source of truth for visual language and component direction.
- Define and apply a distinct design signature early: typography, spacing rhythm, CTA style, section pacing, imagery style, and icon language.
- Build reusable section primitives from homepage patterns, then extend to interior pages.
- Validate homepage quality first (mobile responsiveness, accessibility, performance, trust clarity) before scaling site-wide.
